#. <section class="sutta" id="sn52.2"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn52.2:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 52"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 52"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn52.2:0.2"
msgid "1. Rahogatavagga"
msgstr "1. In Private"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn52.2:0.3"
msgid "2. Dutiyarahogatasutta"
msgstr "2. In Private (2nd)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn52.2:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn52.2:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmato anuruddhassa rahogatassa paṭisallīnassa evaṃ cetaso "
"parivitakko udapādi:"
msgstr "Then as Anuruddha was in private retreat this thought came to his mind:"

msgctxt "sn52.2:1.3"
msgid ""
"“yesaṃ kesañci cattāro satipaṭṭhānā viraddhā, viraddho tesaṃ ariyo maggo "
"sammā dukkhakkhayagāmī;"
msgstr ""
"“Whoever has missed out on these four kinds of mindfulness meditation has "
"missed out on the noble path to the complete ending of suffering."

msgctxt "sn52.2:1.4"
msgid ""
"yesaṃ kesañci cattāro satipaṭṭhānā āraddhā, āraddho tesaṃ ariyo maggo sammā "
"dukkhakkhayagāmī”ti."
msgstr ""
"Whoever has undertaken these four kinds of mindfulness meditation has "
"undertaken the noble path to the complete ending of suffering.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli5.297"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn52.2:2.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno āyasmato anuruddhassa cetasā "
"cetoparivitakkamaññāya—seyyathāpi nāma balavā puriso samiñjitaṃ vā bāhaṃ "
"pasāreyya, pasāritaṃ vā bāhaṃ samiñjeyya; evameva—āyasmato anuruddhassa "
"sammukhe pāturahosi. Atha kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno āyasmantaṃ anuruddhaṃ "
"etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Venerable Mahāmoggallāna knew what Venerable Anuruddha was thinking. As "
"easily as a strong person would extend or contract their arm, he reappeared "
"in front of Anuruddha and said to him:"

msgctxt "sn52.2:2.2"
msgid ""
"“kittāvatā nu kho, āvuso anuruddha, bhikkhuno cattāro satipaṭṭhānā āraddhā "
"hontī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Reverend Anuruddha, how do you define the undertaking of the four kinds of "
"mindfulness meditation by a mendicant?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn52.2:4.1"
msgid ""
"“Idhāvuso, bhikkhu ajjhattaṃ kāye kāyānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno "
"satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Reverend, it’s when a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the "
"body internally—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the "
"world."

msgctxt "sn52.2:4.2"
msgid "Bahiddhā kāye kāyānupassī viharati … pe …"
msgstr "They meditate observing an aspect of the body externally …"

msgctxt "sn52.2:4.3"
msgid ""
"ajjhattabahiddhā kāye kāyānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya "
"loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ."
msgstr ""
"internally and externally—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and "
"aversion for the world."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn52.2:5.1"
msgid ""
"Ajjhattaṃ vedanāsu vedanānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya "
"loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ."
msgstr "They meditate observing an aspect of feelings internally …"

msgctxt "sn52.2:5.2"
msgid ""
"Bahiddhā vedanāsu vedanānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya "
"loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ."
msgstr "externally …"

msgctxt "sn52.2:5.3"
msgid ""
"Ajjhattabahiddhā vedanāsu vedanānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, "
"vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ."
msgstr "internally and externally …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn52.2:6.1"
msgid "Ajjhattaṃ citte … pe …"
msgstr "They meditate observing an aspect of the mind internally …"

msgctxt "sn52.2:6.2"
msgid "bahiddhā citte … pe …"
msgstr "externally …"

msgctxt "sn52.2:6.3"
msgid ""
"ajjhattabahiddhā citte cittānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya "
"loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ."
msgstr "internally and externally …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn52.2:7.1"
msgid "Ajjhattaṃ dhammesu … pe …"
msgstr "They meditate observing an aspect of principles internally …"

msgctxt "sn52.2:7.2"
msgid "bahiddhā dhammesu … pe …"
msgstr "externally …"

msgctxt "sn52.2:7.3"
msgid ""
"ajjhattabahiddhā dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, "
"vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ."
msgstr ""
"internally and externally—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and "
"aversion for the world."

msgctxt "sn52.2:7.4"
msgid "Ettāvatā kho, āvuso, bhikkhuno cattāro satipaṭṭhānā āraddhā hontī”ti."
msgstr ""
"That’s how to define the undertaking of the four kinds of mindfulness "
"meditation by a mendicant.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn52.2:7.5"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
